# Architecture Plan

## Project Shape

Build a Vite + React + TypeScript single-page app for local-first habit tracking. The app should be static-deployable, use strict TypeScript, Tailwind CSS for styling, Zustand for state management with `localStorage` persistence, Vitest/React Testing Library for unit and component tests, and Playwright for the final happy-path E2E test.

## Module Structure

```text
src/
  app/
    App.tsx
    router.tsx
  components/
    habits/
      HabitForm.tsx
      HabitCard.tsx
      HabitList.tsx
      EmptyState.tsx
      CheckInToggle.tsx
      HeatmapCalendar.tsx
      StreakBadge.tsx
      StatsPanel.tsx
    ui/
      ConfirmDialog.tsx
  pages/
    DashboardPage.tsx
    HabitDetailPage.tsx
    NewHabitPage.tsx
  store/
    habitStore.ts
    persistence.ts
    migrations.ts
  types/
    habit.ts
  utils/
    dates.ts
    streaks.ts
    stats.ts
    importExport.ts
  test/
    setup.ts
```

Shared domain types live in `src/types/habit.ts` and should be imported by store, utility, and component modules. Store actions own mutations and persistence. Date, streak, stats, and import/export logic should stay outside React components so they can be tested directly.

